'''Daniel "Dan" Hollander''' (born on May 9, 1972 in [[Royal Oak, Michigan|Royal Oak, MI]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He captured the bronze medal at the [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]] in 1996 and 1997. In 1999, he suffered a number of injuries that forced him to turn professional.
Hollander lives in Michigan and is touring the U.S., {{As of|2008|lc=on}}. He is well known for his comedic skating programs.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}}
